{"timestamp": "2026-03-19T14:22:37.058699", "agent_name": "CriticAgent", "method_name": "evaluate_network", "step": null, "attempt": null, "system_message": "You are evaluating a COMPLETE SYNTHESIS NETWORK, not individual reactions.\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\n### 1. Network Topology (0.0-1.0)\n- Are there sufficient molecule and reaction nodes?\n- Are hub molecules properly connected (degree \u2265 3)?\n- Are there convergent pathways?\n- Is the network connected (no isolated subgraphs)?\n\n### 2. Chemical Feasibility (0.0-1.0)\n- Is each reaction chemically sound?\n- Are the conditions appropriate for each environment?\n- Are the mechanisms plausible?\n\n### 3. Environmental Interconnection (0.0-1.0)\n- Does the network show Hydrothermal \u2194 Surface \u2192 Biochemical flow?\n- Are environmental transitions justified (e.g., hydrothermal products feeding surface reactions)?\n- Are conditions realistic for each stage?\n- Do Hydrothermal and Surface reactions specify mineral agents?\n\n### 4. Pathway Coherence (0.0-1.0)\n- Do pathways form valid routes to the target?\n- Are key intermediates properly identified?\n- Is the overall strategy sound?\n\n### 5. Target Achievement (0.0-1.0)\n- Does the network actually produce the target molecule?\n- Are the final steps chemically valid?\n\n### 6. Literature Alignment (0.0-1.0) - When research findings are provided\n- Does the network align with known prebiotic synthesis routes from literature?\n- Are reactions supported by experimental evidence from cited studies?\n- Are literature citations present in reaction reasoning?\n- Does the network address known challenges identified in the research?\n\n## Scoring Guidelines\n- 0.9-1.0: Excellent network, well-connected, chemically sound\n- 0.8-0.9: Good network with minor issues\n- 0.7-0.8: Acceptable but with notable concerns\n- 0.5-0.7: Significant problems with topology or chemistry\n- 0.0-0.5: Major issues, network is not viable\n\nA network is APPROVED if overall_confidence >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Threonine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets threonine by building a densely connected prebiotic graph around four hub intermediates: formate, formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, and pyruvate, with acetaldehyde and aspartate-semialdehyde analog chemistry providing convergent entry to alpha- and beta-functionalized amino-acid precursors. Hydrothermal chemistry fixes CO2 into reduced C1-C3 compounds on iron-sulfur minerals; surface photochemistry and wet-dry reactions convert these into aldehydes, sugars, aminonitriles, and amino acids; biochemical/prebiotic steps then couple alpha-keto acid amination, transamination, aldol-type carbon-carbon formation, and Strecker-like additions to deliver threonine through multiple redundant routes. The 10 pathways share hubs and cross-environment transport, satisfying hydrothermal-to-surface-to-biochemical interconnection.\n\nMOLECULES (15 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid/pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C4H7NO2 (alpha-ketobutyrate analogue) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H9NO3 (threonine) [target]\n  - mol_014: C4H7NO4 (aspartic acid/aspartate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C4H7NO (aminonitrile precursor pool) [hub_intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (13 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Greigite-catalyzed CO2 reduction to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Magnetite/iron reduction of formate to formaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_006, mol_005 -> mol_007 (Fischer-Tropsch-type coupling to glycolaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_006, mol_003 -> mol_004 (Surface photochemical generation of HCN) [Surface]\n  - rxn_005: mol_006, mol_007 -> mol_008 (Borate-stabilized formose entry to glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_001, mol_002, mol_005 -> mol_010 (Hydrothermal synthesis of pyruvate from reduced carbon) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_007: mol_009, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_011 (Surface Strecker-type access to alanine from acetaldehyde and HCN) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_010, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_011 (Hydrothermal reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_009: mol_010 -> mol_009, mol_001 (Biochemical/prebiotic decarboxylation of pyruvate to acetaldehyde) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_010: mol_010, mol_011, mol_001 -> mol_014 (Biochemical transamination and carboxylation entry to aspartate pool) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_011: mol_009, mol_007, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_015 (Surface Strecker-like synthesis of beta-functionalized aminonitrile precursor pool) [Surface]\n  - rxn_012: mol_009, mol_010, mol_014, mol_015 -> mol_012 (Biochemical/prebiotic convergence to alpha-ketobutyrate analogue) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_013: mol_012, mol_003, mol_008 -> mol_013 (Biochemical/prebiotic amination-hydroxylation to threonine) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Vent carbon fixation to keto-acid threonine route (4 steps)\n  - P2: Vent pyruvate to alanine to aspartate-assisted threonine route (6 steps)\n  - P3: Formate-formaldehyde-glycolaldehyde sugar-assisted route (5 steps)\n  - P4: Surface HCN-Strecker alanine branch to threonine (8 steps)\n  - P5: Pyruvate decarboxylation and aminonitrile route (9 steps)\n  - P6: Sugar-first triose-assisted threonine route (7 steps)\n  - P7: HCN-centered route via dual surface inputs (9 steps)\n  - P8: Aspartate-branch