nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Threonine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network targets threonine through a chemically tighter precursor logic than the failed attempts by making oxaloacetate, aspartate, homoserine, and 2-oxobutanoate the central late-stage intermediates rather than invoking undefined aminonitrile pools or direct aldehyde-to-threonine shortcuts. Hydrothermal chemistry supplies reduced C1/C2/C3 feedstocks (formate, acetate, pyruvate, acetaldehyde) from CO2/CO/H2 on iron-sulfur minerals. Surface chemistry supplies HCN, formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, glyceraldehyde, phosphates, and amino acid precursors under UV, borate stabilization, and wet-dry conditions. Biochemical/prebiotic assembly then channels multiple convergent routes through pyruvate carboxylation-like fixation to oxaloacetate, transamination to aspartate, reduction to homoserine, phosphorylation-like activation, and elimination to 2-oxobutanoate, followed by \u03b2-hydroxylating amination to threonine. Ten pathways are defined as distinct valid traversals through the same connected bipartite graph. Hub molecules are pyruvate, oxaloacetate, aspartate, homoserine, and 2-oxobutanoate.\n\nMOLECULES (21 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H4O2 (acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C4H4O5 (oxaloacetic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H7NO4 (aspartic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C4H9NO3 (homoserine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C4H7NO5P (O-phosphohomoserine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C4H6O3 (2-oxobutyrate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_017: C4H7NO2 (2-aminobutyrate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_018: C4H9NO3 (threonine) [target]\n  - mol_019: H3PO4 (phosphate) [starting]\n  - mol_020: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_021: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (19 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Greigite-catalyzed reduction of carbon dioxide to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_005, mol_002, mol_001 -> mol_006 (Iron-sulfur mediated homologation of formate to acetate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_005, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_010 (Magnetite-catalyzed synthesis of pyruvate from reduced carbon and carbon dioxide) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_010 -> mol_011, mol_001 (Thermal decarboxylation of pyruvate to acetaldehyde) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_005: mol_005 -> mol_007 (UV-TiO2 assisted generation of formaldehyde from formate/carbon dioxide pools) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_007, mol_003 -> mol_004 (Surface photochemical production of HCN via cyanosulfidic chemistry) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_007 -> mol_008 (Borate-stabilized formose entry to glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_008, mol_007 -> mol_009 (Aldol extension of glycolaldehyde to glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_011, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_020 (Surface Strecker-type formation of alanine from acetaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_010, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_020 (Hydrothermal reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_011: mol_010, mol_001 -> mol_012 (Reductive carboxylation-like conversion of pyruvate to oxaloacetate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_012, mol_020 -> mol_013, mol_010 (Transamination of oxaloacetate to aspartate using alanine as amino donor) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_013: mol_013, mol_002 -> mol_014 (Reduction of aspartate-derived carbonyl equivalent to homoserine) [Biochemic